@0=~As you reach the end of the pier running through the Suicide Falls, you notice a couple arguing. The man, dressed in a Dustman's robes, is passionately gesticulating, while the woman accompanying him exudes an unwavering, almost perfect calm.~
@1=~"Darling, *please* be honest with me. Do you not love me anymore?"~
@2=~"Oh, silly, where did you get that idea? Of course I love you." She replies in a soothing voice, absent of intense emotion.~
@4=~Just some lovers' banter. Nothing for you to see here.~
@5=~This woman's calmness is a mask. There is something going on here.~
@6=~Leave.~
@8=~The couple seems to be arguing intensely about something. Their care for each other is evident, but it appears this has been going on for a while. You are faced with a dilemma: should you intervene, or should you leave them to their own devices? After all, it is none of your business.~
@10=~"What are you arguing about?"~
@11=~Listen before you interfere.~
@12=~Leave the lovers to their squabble.~
@14=~The man ignores you.~
@16=~Leave.~
@18=~"Why is it that *every time* I want something more from you, you *never* want it?"~
@19=~The woman looks at him dispassionately before answering. "Because you only desire my body. You're not interested in the metaphysical dimension of love..." Her voice is so blissfully soothing. "Why does love always have to come down to one thing for you? To primitive carnality? To momentary pleasures?"~
@20=~The man seems immune to the woman's soothing voice. "Primitive carnality? Isn't it true that human pleasure is the ultimate good? After all, carnal pleasures are nothing other than... Than..."~
@21=~"A straight path to frustration?"~
@22=~"*A natural expression of the human need for happiness!*"~
@23=~The woman lets the man's words sink in. "My love, your heart burns with passion. But the fire that burns intensely will burn out quickly."~
@24=~"Chief, let's not waste our time on them. It looks like they're having some marital problems... And even if it's not marital, we certainly won't learn anything interesting. We're better off freezing in the Hells."~
@26=~Keep listening.~
@27=~"You're right. Let's go."~
@28=~Leave.~
@30=~The couple continues to argue.~
@32=~Leave them.~
@34=~The man ignores that remark. "I *desire* passion. I want *ecstasy*. A little *romanticism*!"~
@35=~"Why don't you ask what I desire? I want ideal, disembodied love. Moral. Transcendent."~
@36=~"Love is more than a momentary fantasy. It's a repeated daily decision."~
@37=~"Then can't your daily decision be to give me pleasure?"~
@38=~"The guy hit the nail on the head. In my humble opinion, this woman's awfully stiff."~
@39=~"You are wrong, Morte. This woman's assertiveness deserves recognition. No one has the right to force her to push her boundaries, not even her partner. It is her decision."~
@41=~Keep listening.~
@42=~Leave.~
@44=~"So? Can't it?"~
@45=~"Are you unable to control your impulse to remain chaste with me in the name of love?"~
@46=~"This whole abstract description of love makes me sick. Do you really not see how *mundane* love actually is?"~
@48=~"What are you arguing about?"~
@49=~Do not get involved and leave.~
@51=~The man turns to you, and you see resignation in his eyes. "My dear beloved Sonne is as cold as ice towards me..."~
@52=~The woman interrupts him mid-sentence, addressing him in a barely audible voice. "Zack, you really shouldn't involve strangers in our private affairs."~
@53=~"Aye. Let's get out of here."~
@55=~Keep listening.~
@56=~"You're right. Let's go."~
@57=~Do not get involved and leave.~
@59=~The man ignores his beloved, continuing his dilation. "Our argument has been going on for years. Perhaps you, stranger, can talk some sense into her? You look like you've been through a lot."~
@61=~"What exactly am I supposed to do?"~
@62=~"This is not my problem."~
@64=~"Convince *her* to..." He does not manage to finish because his partner interrupts him mid-sentence again.~
@65=~"No! Convince *him*." You detect a hint of irritation in the woman's voice. She is afraid of losing control.~
@67=~"Actually, I don't want to get involved."~
@68=~"Well, I heard your argument and I think I can comment a little."~
@70=~The silenced man looks at you. He seems disappointed.~
@71=~"Suit yourself."~
@72=~"And I was already hopeful."~
@73=~Left by themselves, the couple finds themselves arguing again.~
@75=~Leave.~
@77=~"So? What do you think?"~
@79=~"There are some arguments in favor of Zack..."~
@80=~"There are some arguments in favor of Sonne..."~
@81=~"Do you really have to argue about this on theoretical grounds? Can't you work out some kind of compromise?"~
@82=~"This love of yours is a lie, behind which lies the desire to dominate and control the other's freedom."~
@83=~"Nothing. I have to go."~
@85=~The man looks at you, his mouth agape.~
@86=~"Yes? What arguments?" The woman's mask of calm has begun to melt away.~
@88=~"It's obvious that physical love is something completely natural. You'd have to be crazy to believe all this nonsense about virtue and transcendence."~
@89=~"Devoting oneself to sensuality is also a form of liberation from norms. Rebellion leads to freedom, and freedom... chaos... is the meaning of the multiverse."~
@90=~"Passion is not just a momentary emotion, it is also a path to the continuation of the species. Resisting that is pure selfishness."~
@91=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@93=~"*See*?" the man asks, not bothering to contain his excitement.~
@94=~The woman's face betrays irritation, but she quickly recomposes herself. "You're the same, as you can see. But I'm not convinced of that, not even an inch." The couple turns their attention back to each other and resumes their argument.~
@96=~"Devoting oneself to sensuality is also a form of liberation from norms. Rebellion leads to freedom, and freedom, chaos, is the meaning of the Multiverse."~
@97=~"Passion is not just a momentary emotion, it is also a path to the continuation of the species. Resisting that is pure selfishness."~
@98=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@100=~"Chaos? Well, that is very... abstract, but so is the concept of pure love."~
@101=~"I don't think I can agree with that."~
@103=~"It's obvious that physical love is something completely natural. You'd have to be crazy to believe all this nonsense about virtue and transcendence."~
@104=~"Passion is not just a momentary emotion, it is also a path to the continuation of the species. Resisting that is pure selfishness."~
@105=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@107=~There is a momentary pause in the air after your argument, but as Zack is opening his mouth, his lover asks first:~
@108=~"Hmm... What *exactly* do you mean?" This time you see that the woman is genuinely interested in your words.~
@110=~"If more people thought like you, people would stop being born. What would the multiverse look like, without children?"~
@111=~"Your pursuit of friendship is nothing more than selfishness, for it may ultimately lead to the destruction of humanity. If everyone were as disgustingly self-absorbed as you, the streets of Sigil would be filled with dead people."~
@112=~"I believe that Zack is driven by selfishness too. Taking this into account, I have actually come to a conclusion that Sonne has better arguments..."~
@113=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@115=~A shade of doubt flashes across the woman's face. "These are some brave assumptions."~
@117=~"There's more. Alongside mankind, the love of virtue will die too. Do you think your ideals will live on without someone to follow in your footsteps?"~
@118=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@120=~Sonne pauses for a long moment, unable to find the words to respond. "Well, I think you're exaggerating a bit..."~
@122=~"Be honest, are you going to take your virtues to the grave, or would you rather pass them on to the next generation?"~
@123=~"You know what, you're right. I have changed my mind."~
@125=~The mask of control Sonne has donned instantly slips away, replaced by shame. In her quest for control, she has lost sight of the trap she had set for herself. "You're right. How could I not see how selfish I am?" She turns to her beloved, speaking with a slightly pleading tone. "Zack, forgive me. I'm ready. Take me *here* and *now*!"~
@126=~ "What?" You notice that instead of expected joy, the man's face is filled with disgust. "No way!"~
@127=~"How could I not have noticed, in my stupidity I could *betray* the Dustmen's philosophy... *My* philosophy! And all for some momentary excitement!"~
@128=~"Now that's what I call a *plot twist*."~
@130=~Keep listening.~
@131=~Keep listening.~
@133=~The woman's expression shifts faster than a kaleidoscope. Where shame had been etched a second ago, anger has begun to flare. "Are you kidding? Now that I've realized my mistakes and want to fix them with you, *you* don't want to do this with me anymore?"~
@134=~"That's right. I can't contribute to *cultivating life* any further." He replies, avoiding meeting her gaze.~
@135=~"I'm leaving, Sonne. I must atone in the Mortuary for my impure thoughts."~
@136=~The woman does not answer. The anger on her face fades, giving way to another mask: one of aroused passion. She looks at you with a gaze whose nature you fully understand. "In that case... Can I count on *your* help?"~
@137=~"Chief, you played it smart."~
@138=~"Don't ya even think about it."~
@140=~"Don't drag me into this."~
@141=~"Sure..."~
@142=~"Sure..."~
@144=~The woman's expression shifts faster than a kaleidoscope. Where shame had been etched a second ago, anger has begun to flare. "Are you kidding? Now that I've realized my mistakes and want to fix them with you, *you* don't want to do this with me anymore?"~
@145=~"That's right. I can't contribute to *cultivating life* any further." He replies, avoiding meeting her gaze.~
@146=~"I'm leaving, Sonne. I must atone in the Mortuary for my impure thoughts."~
@147=~"Too bad. Then I'll keep looking." The mask on the woman's face does not waver. "Goodbye."~
@149=~Leave.~
@151=~"Too bad. Then I'll keep looking." The mask on the woman's face does not waver. "Goodbye."~
@153=~Leave.~
@155=~"That was *amazing*. How could I have been so stupid not to try this before?"~
@156=~"I'm going back to the settlement. I still have a lot of work to do to catch up."~
@158=~"Farewell."~
@160=~Before anyone says anything, Annah drags you away from the woman by the shoulder.~
@161=~"No way. We're leavin' now, chit. Not this time, then."~
@162=~"Too bad. Then I'll keep looking." The mask on the woman's face does not waver. "Goodbye."~
@164=~Continue being dragged.~
@166=~"Oh? Like what?"~
@167=~You notice that the woman barely smiled, the corners of her mouth lifting.~
@169=~"Desire and intense emotions inevitably lead to frustrations like yours. Friendship is more stable, so you should calm your passion."~
@170=~"As long as you allow yourself to be driven by passion, you will never rid yourself of the urges of life, and therefore never achieve True Death. You will be constantly reborn. Do you really want that?"~
@171=~"What you call 'love' is nothing more than a simple manifestation of the reproductive instinct. An illusion imposed on individuals to ensure the survival of the species."~
@172=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@174=~"Are you kidding me? Stop lecturing *me* and do what I asked you to do!"~
@175=~The couple begins arguing again.~
@177=~"As long as you allow yourself to be driven by passion, you will never rid yourself of the urges of life, and therefore never achieve True Death. You will be constantly reborn. Do you really want that?"~
@178=~"What you call 'love' is nothing more than a simple manifestation of the reproductive instinct. An illusion imposed on individuals to ensure the survival of the species."~
@179=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@181=~"You're right. I can't contribute to *cultivating life* any further." He replies, avoiding meeting her gaze. "I'm leaving, Sonne. I must atone in the Mortuary for my impure thoughts."
~
@182=~"Wait... I just..."~
@184=~Leave.~
@186=~"Hmm... What *exactly* do you mean?" You see that the man is genuinely curious about your words.~
@188=~"Love can lead to the creation of new life... children. Are you able to accept the ethical consequences of that?"~
@189=~"I don't even have to tell you that love can lead to having children, and I don't think anyone would want that. Giving life is disgusting because everyone awaits death and there is no escape from it."~
@190=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@192=~"No! Not that!"~
@193=~The woman almost explodes with euphoria. "See, Zack?"~
@194=~"Well... It looks like I blundered. Thank you, stranger. Is it time to visit some... temple?"~
@195=~"Almost. Lady Ado has installed a new shrine to her native goddess of happiness through love. We have an invitation, we really should get going."~
@197=~"Farewell."~
@199=~"Compromise? How so?"~
@200=~"Hmm?" The mask of calm on the woman's face gently gives way to a hint of curiosity.~
@202=~"What is love if not an impulse to know the world? Instead of wasting time on pointless arguments, join the Sensates together. They will help you get the most out of your relationship!"~
@203=~"Isn't it true that love begins with physical attraction, but leads to higher forms of relationship? Sonne, give in to it and let yourselves be carried away by passion. And then you will become friends and strive for your virtues."~
@204=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@206=~Both of them look a bit puzzled.~
@207=~"Domination? Hmm..."~
@208=~"So what should we strive for?"~
@210=~"Your approaches are so debilitating. Instead of limiting each other, you should strive for self-fulfillment and strengthen your independence."~
@211=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@213=~The man gasps audibly.~
@214=~"Aye. Do you really think so?"~
@215=~"Chief, that's a trap..."~
@216=~The woman's mask falls, and shock is etched on her face. "What? Zack, are you trying to *enslave* me? Tell me it's not true!"~
@217=~"Of course not... I mean, I'm not trying to do that, but maybe you..."~
@218=~"Me? Of course not!!!" The woman explodes into an overly theatrical outrage, offended by the mere suggestion.~
@219=~Annah spins you around so you look her in the face and repeats herself. "Do you really think so? Do you?"~
@221=~"Yes, of course."~
@222=~"Be quiet, Annah. I'm talking to them right now."~
@223=~Whisper to Annah: "Of course not. But they don't have to know that."~
@224=~"Zack, it's obvious she wants to strip you of your true nature. Will you really let yourself be castrated like that in the name of 'love?' A friend and nothing more? Where is your manly dignity?"~
@225=~"Sonne, can't you see that he's trying to take advantage of you? To make a harlot out of you? He wants to defile your pure nature with his depraved desires?"~
@226=~"You deserve each other. You're stuck in an impasse where each side wants to trap the other and manipulate them."~
@227=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@229=~The couple looks now to you and your argument, distracted briefly.~
@230=~"Oh, I see." She wags her tail with disaffection.~
@231=~"I see. Pike off."~
@232=~"I see..."~
@234=~"Zack, it's obvious she wants to strip you of your true nature. Will you really let yourself be castrated like that in the name of 'love?' A friend and nothing more? Where is your manly dignity?"~
@235=~"Sonne, can't you see that he's trying to take advantage of you? To make a harlot out of you? He wants to defile your pure nature with his depraved desires?"~
@236=~"You deserve each other. You're stuck in an impasse where each side wants to trap the other and manipulate them."~
@237=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@239=~Zack's face is etched with rage. "Sonne, if you think you can make a fool out of me, you're sorely mistaken!"~
@240=~"I don't think so at all! You aren't thinking about leaving me, are you?"~
@242=~"Go out into the world and enjoy yourself. Don't worry about some *prude* who wants to subjugate you."~
@243=~Observe.~
@245=~The man seems enthused by this concept.~
@246=~"Zack, *please* don't listen to him... he's just a random bystander!" The woman's voice grows desperate.~
@247=~"You know what? He's right. There's no point in wasting time on prudes like you. I'll get what you *never* wanted to give me from any harlot. I'm leaving. And I'm not coming back!"~
@248=~Sonne turns back to you. "I hope you're satisfied with what you've done, you rotten berk!"~
@249=~"Aye. That was really mean. On the other hand, the trash took itself out."~
@250=~"Well, it looks like there is one more single lady in the area..."~
@252=~Look as they both leave.~
@254=~"What?! No!"~
@255=~Her expression reveals she had not thought about it before. She was the controlling party in this relationship until a moment ago. "Zack, tell me you're not!"~
@256=~The man is clearly troubled. You will be the judge of his fate.~
@258=~"*Of course* he does. And when he succeeds, he'll look for another one like you. Just look at him. You can see he can't control himself for even fifteen minutes. The question is, how many others have been before you...?"~
@259=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@261=~The man is shocked by your words.~
@262=~The woman's apparent confidence and calm have melted away in an instant. "You swine, how could you? How could I have been so blind as to not see your intentions?"~
@263=~"Bu-but, darling, that's not true! He's lying..."~
@265=~"It's not strange for him to deny it. He's the type of person who, if you grab his hand, will insist that it doesn't belong to him."~
@266=~"Actually, I have changed my mind..."~
@268=~"This is nonsense, *slander!* How can you believe him?!"~
@269=~At these words, Sonne almost falls into despair. "We're done! I should have listened to my mother, saying you weren't right for me." After saying these words, she walks away nervously, trying to hide her tears.~
@270=~"You son of a bitch. I'll kill you for this."~
@272=~Defend yourself.~
@274=~"Is this possible... This cutter is right?"~
@275=~"Indeed, it sounds like it... Of course, it may be a case-by-case scenario... But isn't it worth trying?"~
@276=~"Yes, darling. I like it this way. Let our first moments be intense, and then we'll enjoy peace and stability."~
@277=~They kiss and do not pay attention to you anymore.~
@278=~"That was soo borin'. Makes me wanna puke."~
@280=~Leave.~